  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Devovo ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was only one railroad car at the station building.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The station had been bombed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Nothing else was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we walked about 15 kilometers and crossed a river, Oka-- O-K-A-- on a ferry, which was pulled by a string by two men over the river, and got into a village called Sielce-- S-I-E-L-C-E-- where the Poles 1st Division was being created.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Us, we-- everybody had to walk through a narrow entrance, and there was a fellow in uniform standing there-- Polish uniform-- and he asked everybody for his name.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he, obviously-- I recognized, was Jewish-- and when he saw the name 'Guttmann,' he knew I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he said, you have to write an application that you want to serve in the Polish army or in Polish Division as a volunteer, which I did.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I had arrived, and my unit-- I was assigned to a unit that same day-- and then I arrived in my unit without any papers.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the first thing, when they were writing down all our data, I am asked, what is your ethnicity?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I say, Jewish, because now I am in the Polish army, and I don't want to stay there forever.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So when the war comes to an end, as a Jew, if they don't kick me out, at least I will be able to get out, which was all right.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I stayed with the same unit from June 5, 1940-- between 1943, sorry-- from June 5, 1943, until after the end of the war, until we returned into our barracks in Poland.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "For the last eight months of my service, I was transferred to another unit in, in the [? border guards. ?]",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
